TcExtension.description:
This extension is used in duplicate operation to return NX CAD dependencies that Teamcenter would not be aware of since typically this type of dependency is not published in Teamcenter. This extension can be attached to the fnd0DuplicateExpandOrUpdate operation on BOMLine business object such that when BOMLine is expanded, this extension is automatically triggered to add internal NX CAD dependencies to the expand results.

Availability:
This extension is available for use on fnd0DuplicateExpandOrUpdate operation of BOMLine business object as a Post Action.

Parameters:
bomlines - This is a list of BOMLines that needs to be expanded and queried for CAD dependencies based on the user selected CAD options. CAD dependency queries will be performed on the BOMLines children.
itemRevisions - This is a list of ItemRevisions that needs to be queried for CAD dependencies based on the user selected CAD options.
cadOptions - This is a list of user selected CAD options to perform a query on the bomline or the itemRevisions parameter.
selectionOption - This is a flag for project auto selection. When the value is 1, the system will check the input lines based on the top BOMLine item's project assignment. If any child belongs to the project, then the parent BOMLine will be returned otherwise the parent BOMLine will not be returned. When the value is 0, the operation will do expansion only.
updatedObjects - This is a list of ItemRevisions that needs to be updated in the client UI because it has user selected CAD option Dependencies on them.
cadDependencies - This list contains the dependency information that ties the structure itemRevision to the dependency child. The dependency information are tracked using the Teamcenter::CloneStructureCADDependencyData runtime business object. The new runtime business object will contain the following properties:
Teamcenter::ItemRevision parentObject;
bool parentObjectCloneable;
std::vectorrelatedObjects;
std::vector relatedObjectCloneable;
std::vectorrelatedObjectMandatory;
std::vector relatedObjectGRMName;
std::vectorrelatedObjectCadOptionName;

Sample usage:
Here is an example of how this extension can be used to add CAD dependencies in duplicate operation and add them to expand results. In the BMIDE go to the Extension Rules panel for the BOMLine Business object. Add an extension to the Post Action for the fnd0DuplicateExpandOrUpdate() operation. Save the BMIDE Template, package, and deploy. Launch a Teamcenter client and open assembly to duplicate in Structure Manager application and do Update Display with internal dependencies toggle ON in the duplicate dialog, you will see that the internal CAD dependencies like wave link or inter-part expression which are not published to Teamcenter are added to the duplicate opeartion.
TcExtension.name: NX0Fnd0DuplicateExpandOrUpdatePostActionExt

TcExtension.description:
This extension is used in duplicate operation to update internal NX CAD dependencies that Teamcenter would not be aware of since typically this type of dependency is not published in Teamcenter. This extension can be attached to the fnd0Duplicate operation on BOMLine business object such that when BOMLine is cloned, this extension is automatically triggered to update internal NX CAD dependencies.

Availability:
This extension is available for use on fnd0Duplicate operation of BOMLine business object as a Post Action.

Parameters:
topLine - The parent that will be processed, traversed and cloned during the duplication process. This is BOMLine when running Synchronous mode and ItemRevision when running Asynchronous mode.
topLineResult - This contains the result of the topLine being duplicated. The results are tracked using the Teamcenter::CloneStructureTopLineData runtime business object. The new runtime business object will
Teamcenter::BOMLine bomline;
Teamcenter::ItemRevision orignalItemRev;
Teamcenter::ItemRevision clonedNewItemRev;
int status;

Sample usage:
Here is an example of how this extension can be used to update internal CAD dependencies in duplicate operation. In the BMIDE go to the Extension Rules panel for the BOMLine Business object. Add an extension to the Post Action for the fnd0Duplicate() operation. Save the BMIDE Template, package, and deploy. Launch a Teamcenter client and open assembly to duplicate in Structure Manager application and perform duplicate. When the duplicated assembly in open in NX session with As Saved load option, you will see that the internal CAD references have been updated to point to new cloned data.
TcExtension.name: NX0Fnd0DuplicatePostActionExt
